## 5. Residual gaps

### 5.1 CT still 2.5× over static target

Most of the remaining excess comes from LC-05 weekend coupling — the
solver IS paying the penalty rather than refusing to allocate, which
preserves feasibility. Further tightening would require:
- Per-(resource, segment) LC-05 awareness in the cap logic (complex, was Option B in the pre-implementation assessment)
- OR weight tuning — at weight=100 or 200, CT would drop further but risk solver preferring LC-05 violations if any soft path exists

Both deferred — current behavior is a clear improvement over R3 and a
correct tradeoff.

### 5.2 Merge-results dedupe activity

R4 dropped 27 duplicate RT/CT rows (R3 had 0, R2 had 50). The tighter
objective pressure from the penalty is producing more overlap candidates
at sub-partition boundaries. Safety-net dedupe catches them cleanly;
no bad rows reach the output. The underlying
`_split_oversized_partition` overlap pattern is worth a dedicated look,
but not a regression of Fix #13 — the pattern predates this batch.

### 5.3 Solve time +86%

Adding 524 int vars and 524 linear constraints to the CP-SAT model
slows presolve and search. At 143s of solve (well within the 1,800s
budget) this is an acceptable cost for the correctness gain. If larger
scopes push solve time past a useful threshold, `REST_DAY_EXCESS_PENALTY_WEIGHT = 0`
reverts instantly.

